property_details: Welcome to Peninsula Sarasota condos, a limited collection of exceptional residences in an intimate setting overlooking Sarasota Bay. All within walking distance of Sarasota’s vibrant downtown lifestyle, beautiful beaches and Florida’s most dynamic arts-and-culture scene. From the moment you step off your private elevator directly into your private residence’s foyer, you’ll be enveloped in one of the most expansive yet intimate of all Sarasota condos. As one of just 23 luxury residences, privacy abounds. The sprawling, open design, calming décor, and spa-inspired color palette instantly convey a soothing sense of relaxation. Soaring 10-foot ceilings, windows, and glass doors showcase sweeping vistas throughout your Sarasota home. Blissful experiences transpire in every room because this relaxing, contemporary aesthetic is carried through each area. In the carefully curated, open-plan designer kitchen, you’ll discover sleek European-inspired cabinetry, Quartz countertops, a dramatic waterfall island, Gaggenau appliances, Rohl plumbing fixtures, designer finishes, and every new technology that enhances care and convenience. Optional Bio-fuel fireplaces and feature walls add warmth and detail, while wraparound terraces with built-in gas grills extend living and entertaining to the sky. Whether you choose a 3-bedroom or 3-bedroom plus den floor plan, every residence includes hardwood or large-format porcelain-tile floors throughout. All primary suites include expansive walk-in closets and spa-like bath retreats with roomy soaking tubs and glass-enclosed, walk-in showers.
amenity_details: Amenities include: Private resort-style swimming pool, firepits and sun deck with entertainment areas for resident’s enjoyment located on the second floor connecting the two buildings; On-site knowledgeable concierge for residents personalized service and assistance; State-of-the-art Fitness Center featuring the latest high-tech cardio and strength equipment; Resident’s mail room with ample space for package storage; Secured Wi-Fi throughout all common areas; Pet friendly community; 24/7 access-controlled entry points at all elevators, lobbies, and parking garage; Rooftop Residents’ Lounge Overlooking Marina Jack and Sarasota Bay; Spacious gathering room for private events, including a Wine Storage Room and elegant waterfall edge bar; Individual, lockable resident storage; Convenient kayak, paddle board, and bike storage; Common area design by KAS – Karen Asprea Studio of New York creating a tranquil, spa-like sanctuary
developer_details: A six-generation family business, Gault Family Companies has over 160 years of knowledge in the development industry. As President, Sam operates three business divisions in the Westport, Connecticut area: Energy & Homes Solutions, Stone & Landscape Supplies and Properties & Development. The company has a storied history in real estate development and management, with a healthy property portfolio. Sam has earned a solid reputation for identifying and developing value in commercial, residential, retail, office spaces, and respectfully repurposing historic landmark buildings.
architect_details: Ensuring an exceptional, next-level design, the partners have commissioned the architecture firm Hoyt Architects. Based in Sarasota, Hoyt Architects is renowned for their experiential and innovative approach to design, creating immersive residential spaces unlike any other. Founding principal Gary Hoyt is also credited with shaping the vision of the Quay Sarasota, a bustling dining, shopping, and entertainment district within walking distance of Peninsula Sarasota. Hoyt’s impressive portfolio in the Downtown Sarasota area also includes The Mark, Sansara, and The Jewel.
designer_details: Chelsea Dunbar is a Sarasota-based interior designer that has worked for over 15 years on both commercial and residential projects. She is an NCIDQ-certified designer and holds a BFA degree in Interior Design from the Savannah College of Art and Design. Focused on providing a highly personalized level of service with keen attention to detail, she has earned the trust of more than 150 residential clients and counting throughout Sarasota, Siesta Key, and Largo, Florida. At Peninsula Sarasota, Dunbar will assist future homeowners with all of their design needs, selecting the features and finishes that complement each owner’s specific lifestyle wishes.
